-- Zimbabwe’s Government Plans to Offer 25% of Contracts to Youths
-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a   a n d   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-06-12T14:59:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/zimbabwe-s-government-plans-to-offer-25-of-contracts-to-youths.html
The Zimbabwean government will from
now allocate 25 percent of all contracts to people under the age
of 35, Indigenization Minister  Saviour Kasukuwere  said.  The plan has been approved by the southern African nation’s
Cabinet, Kasukuwere said at a meeting of the Zimbabwe Youth
Council today in Harare, the capital.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Brian Latham via Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net ;
